                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine, regular, by a well-trained hand.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        <date>Second half of the 16th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; a few lines on the incipit page of all
                           texts; incipits and headings of Gospel chapters and minor texts; short
                           postscript to the Gospel of Matthew; chapter numbers and titles and the
                           word mǝʿrāf; numbers of the “tituli”; elements of the punctuation signs;
                           Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#145v">f. 145v: </locus>
                        <desc>Crosses.</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"/>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#2r">f. 2r</locus>
                           <desc>: Ownership or donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Names of the owners/donors (possibly also other proper names)
                              erased. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#2r">f. 2r</locus>
                           <desc>: Record concerning a litigation about inheritance issues.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> In Amharic. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#2v">f. 2v</locus>
                           <desc>: Transaction note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> In Amharic. Dated 18 Ḫǝdār, 1942 year of mercy (=
                           27 November 1949 A.D.). Kahsay Walda Māryām mentioned in the text may be
                           the same person as ʾato<note> Kahsay in Additio 7. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#43v">f. 43v</locus>
                           <desc>: Short prayers with ʾasmat for different day times (?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is partly erased. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#67ra">f. 67ra</locus>
                           <desc>-vb: Excerpt from the Ṣalota ʿǝṭān(?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in a neat, careful secondary hand. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus target="#143r">f. 143r</locus>
                           <desc>: Transaction note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> In Amharic. Dated 7 Sane 1937 year of mercy (= 14
                           June, 1945 A.D.). ʾAto<note> Dästa Gabra ʾAragāwi mentioned in the note
                              is evidently the same person as the seller in Additio 8. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a7">
                           <locus target="#143v">f. 143v</locus>
                           <desc>: Record concerning a litigation.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> Written in a well trained hand in Amharic. Parts
                           of the note have been erased. The note mentions a number of localities,
                           including May ʾAbʿa, ʾAndel, Gǝlamo. ʾAto<note> Kahsay mentioned at the
                              end of the text may be the same person as Kahsay Walda Māryām in
                              Additio 3. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a8">
                           <locus target="#144v">f. 144v</locus>
                           <desc>: Transaction note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> In Amharic. Dated 29 Naḥāse 1919 year of mercy (=
                           4 September 1927 A.D.). ʾAto<note> Dästa Gabra ʾAragāwi mentioned in the
                              note is evidently the same person as the seller in Additio 6. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Writing exercise (fragment of the genealogy of Christ in
                           Mt. 1): <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>.
 - Traces of stamps: <locus target="#3r">3r</locus>, 5r, 36v, 84v, 85r, 110v.
 - Notes in the
                           upper margin repeating chapter titles or summarizing chapter contents:
                              <locus target="#4v">4v</locus>, 5r, 6r, 6v, 10v, 11r, etc.
 -
                           Crude liturgical note: <locus target="#116v">116v</locus>.
 - Writing
                           exercise: <locus target="#145v">145v</locus>.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Threads are inserted in the upper right corner:
                              fols. 44, 94, 130.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
